00:49:51,628 --> 00:49:55,080
<i>You weren't in broadcasting
or journalism or anything like that?</i>

728
00:49:56,216 --> 00:50:00,297
Believe it or not, I studied
19th-century French poetry.

729
00:50:17,237 --> 00:50:18,518
You speak French!

730
00:50:24,370 --> 00:50:27,039
<i>I haven't done this since I was a kid.</i>

731
00:50:27,289 --> 00:50:29,081
<i>Me neither. It's fun!</i>

732
00:50:29,541 --> 00:50:30,407
Clean fun.

733
00:50:33,295 --> 00:50:36,795
I hope one day I can do this
with my own children.

734
00:50:40,219 --> 00:50:42,461
<i>Where'd you get that?</i>

735
00:50:42,721 --> 00:50:45,343
Well, I went over
to the snowman shop.

736
00:50:47,184 --> 00:50:48,726
Hey, an assassin!

737
00:50:49,186 --> 00:50:50,764
<i>I'll protect you!</i>

738
00:50:51,272 --> 00:50:54,023
I shall die for you.
You shall not take her!

739
00:50:54,233 --> 00:50:55,513
Find cover!

740
00:50:57,862 --> 00:51:00,187
<i>I'm getting some good ones.</i>

741
00:51:00,406 --> 00:51:03,276
<i>That's a boy! Good try.</i>

742
00:51:03,492 --> 00:51:05,152
Help me!

743
00:52:01,133 --> 00:52:02,296
What?

744
00:52:02,551 --> 00:52:06,596
<i>I'm just amazed,
and I'm not easily amazed.</i>

745
00:52:06,847 --> 00:52:08,258
About what?

746
00:52:08,516 --> 00:52:11,267
How you can start a day with one
kind of expectation...

747
00:52:11,477 --> 00:52:13,553
...and end up
so completely different.

748
00:52:14,981 --> 00:52:18,147
Do you like the way
this day is turning out?

749
00:52:18,359 --> 00:52:20,767
I like it very much.

750
00:52:21,028 --> 00:52:24,528
<i>It's a perfect day.
You couldn't plan a day like this.</i>

751
00:52:24,782 --> 00:52:26,027
Well, you can.

752
00:52:26,242 --> 00:52:29,243
It just takes an awful lot of work.

753
00:52:29,495 --> 00:52:31,701
Come in.
I want to show you something.

754
00:52:31,914 --> 00:52:34,203
<i>- I don't think I should.
- I agree.</i>

755
00:52:34,458 --> 00:52:38,788
<i>That's why I want to show you one thing,
then kick you right out.</i>

756
00:52:46,971 --> 00:52:49,213
<i>It's just lovely.</i>

757
00:52:59,609 --> 00:53:02,360
Would you like to sit
and stare at the fake fire?

758
00:53:07,033 --> 00:53:09,239
<i>It's a really wonderful room.</i>

759
00:53:09,493 --> 00:53:11,320
It is now.

760
00:53:18,252 --> 00:53:20,708
<i>I don't think we should do this.</i>

761
00:53:20,963 --> 00:53:22,588
<i>I don't either.</i>

762
00:53:25,301 --> 00:53:28,006
On second thought,
I think we should.

763
00:53:28,846 --> 00:53:32,013
<i>It's the perfect end
to a perfect day.</i>

764
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:35,517
<i>Well, it's a little fast for me.</i>

765
00:53:35,770 --> 00:53:37,181
Me too.

766
00:53:37,647 --> 00:53:39,889
Maybe I should go.

767
00:53:40,108 --> 00:53:42,017
Where would you go?

768
00:53:42,276 --> 00:53:43,652
Why?

769
00:53:43,861 --> 00:53:46,150
<i>We've got a perfect fire.</i>

770
00:53:46,447 --> 00:53:49,484
<i>I've got some French poetry here.
Baudelaire...</i>

771
00:53:51,035 --> 00:53:52,529
I will read to you.

772
00:53:53,287 --> 00:53:57,415
<i>I've got some ice cream on
the windowsill. Hold on a minute.</i>

773
00:54:03,047 --> 00:54:04,078
Rocky road.

774
00:54:04,340 --> 00:54:05,882
I love rocky road.

775
00:54:06,134 --> 00:54:08,043
Yeah, I thought so.

776
00:54:08,344 --> 00:54:10,052
You have to stay.

777
00:54:10,304 --> 00:54:14,088
<i>No, really, I'm tired.
We can see each other tomorrow.</i>

778
00:54:14,350 --> 00:54:18,099
<i>No, tonight.
It's got to be tonight.</i>

779
00:54:18,312 --> 00:54:21,183
No, Phil, really.

780
00:54:22,108 --> 00:54:25,358
Just stay for a while and
if you like it, stay longer.

781
00:54:25,570 --> 00:54:27,693
And if you like that, stay longer.

782
00:54:27,905 --> 00:54:29,779
<i>Let's not spoil it, okay?</i>

783
00:54:30,033 --> 00:54:32,440
<i>I don't want to spoil it either.</i>

784
00:54:32,660 --> 00:54:35,578
<i>You know I can't stay with you.</i>

785
00:54:35,830 --> 00:54:38,914
Why not? I love you.

786
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:43,083
You love me?

787
00:54:43,338 --> 00:54:47,466
<i>- You don't even know me.
- I know you.</i>

788
00:54:49,010 --> 00:54:51,964
<i>Oh, no. I can't believe
I fell for this!</i>

789
00:54:52,221 --> 00:54:54,594
This whole day has been
one long setup.

790
00:54:54,849 --> 00:54:55,798
<i>No, it hasn't.</i>

791
00:54:56,059 --> 00:54:58,810
And I hate fudge. Yuck!

792
00:54:59,103 --> 00:55:01,143
No white chocolate, no fudge.

793
00:55:01,731 --> 00:55:05,147
What are you doing?
Are you making some kind of list?

794
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:08,563
Did you call my friends
and ask them what I like?

795
00:55:08,821 --> 00:55:12,321
- Is this what love is for you?
- This is real. This is love.

796
00:55:12,534 --> 00:55:13,992
Stop saying that!

797
00:55:14,619 --> 00:55:16,161
You must be crazy.

798
00:55:16,412 --> 00:55:20,113
<i>I could never love you because
you'll never love anyone but yourself.</i>

799
00:55:20,667 --> 00:55:24,249
<i>I don't even like myself.
Give me another chance.</i>

800
00:55:25,922 --> 00:55:28,543
<i>That's for making me
care about you.</i>

801
00:55:35,515 --> 00:55:37,970
<i>I haven't done this
since I was a kid.</i>

802
00:55:38,226 --> 00:55:39,222
<i>It's fun!</i>

803
00:55:39,435 --> 00:55:43,765
<i>And good, clean fun too.
That's what's missing in the world.</i>

804
00:55:44,023 --> 00:55:46,728
<i>I can't wait to do this
with my own children.</i>

805
00:55:46,943 --> 00:55:48,485
I want lots of kids!

806
00:55:48,736 --> 00:55:52,568
I want to adopt, I want my own kids,
I want to have foster kids.

807
00:55:52,824 --> 00:55:55,066
I got this at Snowman City.

808
00:55:55,326 --> 00:55:58,162
Hey! Some kid just
threw a snowball at us.

809
00:55:58,413 --> 00:56:01,248
<i>Come here! Let's have some fun!</i>

810
00:56:03,460 --> 00:56:06,247
I wish these were my own kids.

811
00:56:08,882 --> 00:56:11,503
Are any of you up for adoption?

812
00:56:12,218 --> 00:56:14,626
<i>Here's a humdinger over here!</i>

813
00:56:14,888 --> 00:56:16,927
<i>Wasn't that great?</i>

814
00:56:25,357 --> 00:56:26,981
Stop it!

815
00:57:11,778 --> 00:57:13,771
Phil! Over here!

816
00:57:16,157 --> 00:57:18,779
<i>Where have you been?
You're missing the fun.</i>

817
00:57:19,035 --> 00:57:20,909
Phil, you look terrible.

818
00:57:21,580 --> 00:57:24,071
What happened? Rough night?

819
00:57:42,309 --> 00:57:43,969
Okay, campers.

820
00:57:44,394 --> 00:57:46,221
Rise and shine.

821
00:57:48,148 --> 00:57:51,813
<i>Don't forget your booties,
because it's cold out there.</i>

822
00:57:52,736 --> 00:57:55,143
<i>It's cold out there every day.</i>

823
00:57:55,864 --> 00:57:59,696
<i>This country's largest lake,
Chapala, is located near Guadalajara,</i>

824
00:58:00,869 --> 00:58:01,948
What is Mexico?

825
00:58:02,162 --> 00:58:03,193
<i>What is Mexico?</i>

826
00:58:03,538 --> 00:58:05,365
<i>- Correct,
- Lakes and Rivers, 400,</i>

827
00:58:05,624 --> 00:58:08,293
<i>Seneca is the largest
of these lakes,</i>

828
00:58:08,960 --> 00:58:10,455
What are the Finger Lakes?

829
00:58:10,670 --> 00:58:13,624
<i>- What are the Finger Lakes?
- Correct,</i>

830
00:58:13,840 --> 00:58:18,004
<i>- This lake in Bolivia...
- What is Titicaca?</i>

831
00:58:18,261 --> 00:58:20,005
<i>- What is Titicaca?
- Correct,</i>

832
00:58:20,222 --> 00:58:21,171
For 1,000.

833
00:58:21,389 --> 00:58:23,299
<i>- Milky-coloured...
- The Rhone.</i>

834
00:58:23,558 --> 00:58:25,183
<i>,,, when entering Lake Geneva,,,</i>

835
00:58:25,435 --> 00:58:27,973
<i>,,, this river is
clear blue upon exiting,</i>

836
00:58:28,188 --> 00:58:29,137
<i>- Jim?
- The Rhone,</i>

837
00:58:29,398 --> 00:58:30,726
<i>Good for $1, 000,</i>

838
00:58:30,982 --> 00:58:33,390
<i>You're $500 off the lead right now,</i>

839
00:58:36,196 --> 00:58:37,856
This is pitiful.

840
00:58:38,198 --> 00:58:39,609
A thousand people...

841
00:58:39,866 --> 00:58:42,867
...freezing their butts off,
waiting to worship a rat.

842
00:58:43,078 --> 00:58:44,656
What a hype.

843
00:58:45,330 --> 00:58:49,375
They used to pull the hog out,
and they used to eat it.

844
00:58:49,584 --> 00:58:52,704
<i>You're hypocrites! All of you!</i>

845
00:58:55,007 --> 00:58:56,549
You got a problem, Larry?

846
00:58:58,010 --> 00:58:58,840
Untie your tongue.

847
00:58:59,052 --> 00:59:01,424
Come here and talk.
Am I upsetting you...

848
00:59:01,638 --> 00:59:02,836
...princess?

849
00:59:03,056 --> 00:59:04,848
You want a prediction
about the weather?

850
00:59:05,100 --> 00:59:07,769
<i>You're asking the wrong Phil.</i>

851
00:59:08,020 --> 00:59:10,689
<i>I'll give you a winter prediction.</i>

852
00:59:10,939 --> 00:59:12,979
<i>It's going to be cold.</i>

853
00:59:13,233 --> 00:59:15,440
<i>It's going to be gray.</i>

854
00:59:15,652 --> 00:59:20,445
<i>And it's going to last you
for the rest of your life.</i>

855
00:59:55,275 --> 00:59:59,024
Once again the eyes of the nation
have turned here...

856
00:59:59,530 --> 01:00:02,780
...to this tiny village
in Western Pennsylvania.

857
01:00:02,991 --> 01:00:05,909
There is no way that this winter...

858
01:00:06,161 --> 01:00:09,032
...is ever going to end...

859
01:00:09,248 --> 01:00:13,197
...as long as this groundhog
keeps seeing his shadow.

860
01:00:13,460 --> 01:00:15,334
<i>I don't see any other way out.</i>

861
01:00:16,130 --> 01:00:18,003
<i>He's got to be stopped.</i>

862
01:00:19,508 --> 01:00:20,883
And I have to stop it.

863
01:00:23,428 --> 01:00:24,258
Real good, Phil.

864
01:00:24,513 --> 01:00:25,758
Real good.

865
01:00:27,349 --> 01:00:28,927
<i>He's out of his gourd.</i>

866
01:00:33,605 --> 01:00:36,974
<i>I'm worried. There's something
really wrong with Phil.</i>

867
01:00:37,234 --> 01:00:39,903
<i>There's a lot of things
wrong with Phil.</i>

868
01:00:42,072 --> 01:00:43,317
Hi, Phil.

869
01:00:43,741 --> 01:00:45,863
<i>I've come to the end of me.</i>

870
01:00:46,118 --> 01:00:48,241
<i>There's no way out now.</i>

871
01:00:49,705 --> 01:00:53,038
Just remember, we had
a beautiful day together once.

872
01:00:56,462 --> 01:00:57,872
All right, little fellow.

873
01:00:58,130 --> 01:01:01,499
Good job. He just smiled at me!
Did you see that?

874
01:01:01,759 --> 01:01:03,253
I believe he did.

875
01:01:04,178 --> 01:01:07,013
Okay, little fellow.
There you go.

876
01:01:09,016 --> 01:01:11,388
Hi, there. Something I can
do you for?

877
01:01:13,979 --> 01:01:15,888
Hey! What are you doing?

878
01:01:20,653 --> 01:01:22,692
Get the word out.
Somebody kidnapped Phil!

879
01:01:23,072 --> 01:01:24,400
We are going after him!

880
01:01:31,080 --> 01:01:33,487
Why would anybody steal a groundhog?

881
01:01:33,958 --> 01:01:35,784
I could think of reasons.

882
01:01:36,001 --> 01:01:36,950
Pervert.

883
01:02:02,987 --> 01:02:04,778
He must have just snapped!

884
01:02:04,989 --> 01:02:06,317
This ought to be good.

885
01:02:08,701 --> 01:02:09,946
What is he doing?

886
01:02:10,160 --> 01:02:11,703
What can he be thinking?

887
01:02:12,371 --> 01:02:13,949
Not bad for a quadruped.

888
01:02:14,206 --> 01:02:18,121
Check your mirrors. Side of your eye.
Side of your eye.

889
01:02:24,175 --> 01:02:25,669
<i>That's it.</i>

890
01:02:25,926 --> 01:02:28,963
<i>Hey, they're chasing us!
Come on, make it fun.</i>

891
01:02:37,188 --> 01:02:38,350
<i>Don't drive angry.</i>

892
01:02:38,564 --> 01:02:39,762
<i>Don't drive angry.</i>

893
01:02:59,794 --> 01:03:02,664
<i>There's no way out
except the way we came in!</i>

894
01:03:02,922 --> 01:03:04,380
We got him now!

895
01:03:23,693 --> 01:03:24,891
What is he doing?

896
01:03:25,152 --> 01:03:26,148
<i>I don't know.</i>

897
01:03:30,491 --> 01:03:33,278
<i>If you got to shoot,
don't hit the groundhog.</i>

898
01:03:38,082 --> 01:03:39,825
<i>Mustn't keep them waiting.</i>

899
01:03:43,170 --> 01:03:44,499
<i>It's showtime.</i>

900
01:03:50,886 --> 01:03:52,167
On me in three...

901
01:03:54,307 --> 01:03:55,137
...two...

902
01:03:57,059 --> 01:03:58,008
...one.

903
01:04:11,824 --> 01:04:12,855
Phil!

904
01:04:15,202 --> 01:04:16,578
He might be okay.

905
01:04:21,209 --> 01:04:23,746
Well, no. Probably not now.

906
01:04:39,393 --> 01:04:40,638
Nuts.

907
01:04:48,569 --> 01:04:51,487
Did you sleep well, Mr. Connors?

908
01:04:52,532 --> 01:04:54,192
Would you like...

909
01:04:54,826 --> 01:04:56,236
...some toast?

910
01:05:14,595 --> 01:05:16,671
Oh, my God!

911
01:05:49,255 --> 01:05:50,630
<i>That's him.</i>

912
01:05:53,801 --> 01:05:57,217
He was a really, really great guy.

913
01:05:57,472 --> 01:05:59,180
I really, really liked him...

914
01:05:59,599 --> 01:06:00,630
...a lot.

915
01:06:07,982 --> 01:06:09,975
<i>I'm sorry?
What was that again?</i>

916
01:06:10,401 --> 01:06:13,153
<i>- I'm a god.
- You're God?</i>

917
01:06:13,363 --> 01:06:16,613
<i>I'm a god. I'm not the god,
I don't think.</i>

918
01:06:17,200 --> 01:06:19,323
Because you survived a car wreck?

919
01:06:19,535 --> 01:06:20,698
You folks ready to order?

920
01:06:20,954 --> 01:06:24,157
<i>I didn't just survive a wreck.
I wasn't just blown up.</i>

921
01:06:24,582 --> 01:06:27,156
I have been stabbed,
shot, poisoned...

922
01:06:27,377 --> 01:06:30,710
...frozen, hung, electrocuted
and burned.

923
01:06:30,922 --> 01:06:32,250
Oh, really.

924
01:06:32,507 --> 01:06:36,718
Every morning I wake up without a
scratch, not a dent in the fender.

925
01:06:37,428 --> 01:06:38,508
I am an immortal.

926
01:06:38,721 --> 01:06:41,343
Special today is blueberry waffles.

927
01:06:41,558 --> 01:06:43,384
Why are you telling me this?

928
01:06:43,685 --> 01:06:45,808
Because I want you to believe in me.

929
01:06:46,020 --> 01:06:47,349
You are not a god.

930
01:06:47,564 --> 01:06:50,979
<i>Take my word. It's 12 years
of Catholic school talking.</i>

931
01:06:51,526 --> 01:06:53,483
<i>I can come back if you're not ready.</i>

932
01:06:53,695 --> 01:06:55,687
<i>How do you know I'm not a god?</i>

933
01:06:55,905 --> 01:06:57,150
Please.

934
01:06:57,407 --> 01:06:59,732
<i>- How do you know?
- It's not possible.</i>

935
01:06:59,951 --> 01:07:01,694
<i>I'll come back.</i>

936
01:07:02,036 --> 01:07:03,281
Doris.

937
01:07:06,708 --> 01:07:09,281
This is Doris.
Her brother-in-law owns this diner.

938
01:07:09,544 --> 01:07:13,209
<i>She's worked here since she was 17.
She wants to see Paris...</i>

939
01:07:13,423 --> 01:07:14,621
...before she dies.

940
01:07:14,841 --> 01:07:15,790
Boy, would I!

941
01:07:16,009 --> 01:07:18,678
- What are you doing?
- Debbie and her fiancé.

942
01:07:18,928 --> 01:07:20,173
Do I know you?

943
01:07:20,388 --> 01:07:23,259
<i>They're supposed to get married.
She's having second thoughts.</i>

944
01:07:23,516 --> 01:07:24,679
What?

945
01:07:24,934 --> 01:07:26,049
Lovely ring.

946
01:07:26,311 --> 01:07:31,138
<i>Bill's been a waiter three years,
since he left Penn State to work.</i>

947
01:07:31,399 --> 01:07:34,484
<i>He likes the town,
paints toy soldiers, and he's gay.</i>

948
01:07:34,694 --> 01:07:35,725
I am.

949
01:07:36,362 --> 01:07:39,114
<i>Gus hates it here,
wishes he'd stayed in the Navy.</i>

950
01:07:39,365 --> 01:07:41,903
<i>I could've retired
on half pay after 20 years.</i>

951
01:07:42,160 --> 01:07:43,987
Excuse me. Is this a trick?

952
01:07:44,245 --> 01:07:48,077
<i>Maybe the real God uses tricks.
Maybe he's not omnipotent...</i>

953
01:07:48,333 --> 01:07:50,242
...he just knows everything.

954
01:07:50,502 --> 01:07:51,830
<i>- Who's that?
- Tom.</i>

955
01:07:52,087 --> 01:07:54,079
He worked in the coal mine
till it closed.

956
01:07:54,297 --> 01:07:55,460
- And her?
- Alice.

957
01:07:55,715 --> 01:07:58,253
Came from Ireland when she
was a baby. Lived in Erie.

958
01:07:58,510 --> 01:07:59,340
<i>He's right.</i>

959
01:07:59,552 --> 01:08:00,963
- And her?
- Nancy.

960
01:08:01,221 --> 01:08:05,171
Works in a shop, makes noises like
a chipmunk when she gets excited.

961
01:08:05,433 --> 01:08:07,141
<i>- It's true.
- How do you know this?</i>

962
01:08:07,394 --> 01:08:09,102
I told you, I know everything.

963
01:08:09,354 --> 01:08:12,224
In five seconds, a waiter
will drop a tray.

964
01:08:12,440 --> 01:08:15,192
- Five, four, three, two, one.
- This is nuts.

965
01:08:17,529 --> 01:08:19,936
<i>- Okay?
- Okay, that's enough.</i>

966
01:08:20,991 --> 01:08:23,197
What about me?
Do you know me too?

