01:08:23,451 --> 01:08:27,663
I know all about you. You hope
for more than Channel 9 Pittsburgh.

968
01:08:27,872 --> 01:08:30,280
Well, everyone knows that.

969
01:08:30,667 --> 01:08:33,240
You like boats but not the ocean.

970
01:08:33,670 --> 01:08:37,039
You go to a lake in the summer
with your family.

971
01:08:37,299 --> 01:08:41,213
<i>There's a dock and a boathouse
with boards missing from the roof...</i>

972
01:08:41,928 --> 01:08:44,846
...and a place you used to
crawl underneath to be alone.

973
01:08:45,473 --> 01:08:48,724
<i>You're a sucker for
French poetry and rhinestones.</i>

974
01:08:49,436 --> 01:08:50,847
<i>You're very generous.</i>

975
01:08:51,104 --> 01:08:53,595
<i>You're kind to strangers
and children.</i>

976
01:08:54,149 --> 01:08:56,984
When you stand in the snow
you look like an angel.

977
01:08:57,444 --> 01:08:58,986
How are you doing this?

978
01:09:00,071 --> 01:09:03,025
I told you. I wake up every day.

979
01:09:03,283 --> 01:09:04,943
Right here.

980
01:09:05,160 --> 01:09:08,576
<i>Right in Punxsutawney.
And it's always February 2nd.</i>

981
01:09:09,581 --> 01:09:12,072
<i>And there's nothing
I can do about it.</i>

982
01:09:12,792 --> 01:09:15,877
<i>If you still can't believe me, listen:</i>

983
01:09:16,129 --> 01:09:18,122
In 10 seconds...

984
01:09:18,632 --> 01:09:22,083
...Larry is going to come
and take you away from me.

985
01:09:22,344 --> 01:09:24,171
<i>But you can't let him.</i>

986
01:09:25,180 --> 01:09:28,216
<i>Please believe me.
You've got to believe me.</i>

987
01:09:33,313 --> 01:09:37,311
You guys ready? We better go,
to stay ahead of the weather.

988
01:09:37,943 --> 01:09:39,188
<i>What's that?</i>

989
01:09:40,112 --> 01:09:42,519
<i>"... to stay ahead of the weather."</i>

990
01:09:48,036 --> 01:09:52,116
Maybe it really is happening.
How else could you know so much?

991
01:09:52,332 --> 01:09:54,823
<i>There is no way.
I'm not that smart.</i>

992
01:09:55,961 --> 01:09:58,203
Maybe I should
spend the day with you...

993
01:09:58,463 --> 01:10:01,915
...as an objective witness,
just to see what happens.

994
01:10:02,175 --> 01:10:04,631
This sounds like a science project.

995
01:10:05,762 --> 01:10:06,960
Concentrate.

996
01:10:07,222 --> 01:10:09,013
You got to want it.

997
01:10:09,474 --> 01:10:11,550
You got to want it, Rita.

998
01:10:12,019 --> 01:10:15,886
<i>Come on. It's more
in the wrist than the fingers.</i>

999
01:10:24,197 --> 01:10:26,024
Be the hat. Come on, go.

1000
01:10:26,283 --> 01:10:29,237
<i>- It'd take me a year to get good.
- Six months.</i>

1001
01:10:29,494 --> 01:10:32,745
<i>Four to five hours a day,
and you'd be an expert.</i>

1002
01:10:33,248 --> 01:10:36,866
- Is this what you do with eternity?
- Now you know.

1003
01:10:38,295 --> 01:10:40,334
<i>That's not the worst part.</i>

1004
01:10:40,589 --> 01:10:42,000
<i>What's the worst part?</i>

1005
01:10:42,257 --> 01:10:44,250
The worst part is that...

1006
01:10:44,468 --> 01:10:47,006
<i>...tomorrow you'll have
forgotten all about this...</i>

1007
01:10:47,262 --> 01:10:49,469
<i>...and you'll treat me
like a jerk again.</i>

1008
01:10:50,599 --> 01:10:52,058
I am a jerk.

1009
01:10:52,267 --> 01:10:54,094
<i>No, you're not.</i>

1010
01:10:54,478 --> 01:10:58,974
<i>It doesn't make any difference.
I've killed myself so many times...</i>

1011
01:10:59,233 --> 01:11:00,940
<i>...I don't even exist anymore.</i>

1012
01:11:01,526 --> 01:11:04,278
Sometimes I wish I had
a thousand lifetimes.

1013
01:11:04,863 --> 01:11:07,864
<i>I don't know.
Maybe it's not a curse.</i>

1014
01:11:08,116 --> 01:11:10,738
It just depends
on how you look at it.

1015
01:11:12,287 --> 01:11:14,494
<i>Gosh, you're an upbeat lady!</i>

1016
01:11:17,793 --> 01:11:20,960
<i>I want you to know it's been
a really nice day for me.</i>

1017
01:11:21,213 --> 01:11:22,078
Me too.

1018
01:11:22,297 --> 01:11:23,495
And maybe...

1019
01:11:23,757 --> 01:11:27,422
<i>...if it's not too boring,
we can do it again sometime.</i>

1020
01:11:27,678 --> 01:11:29,088
I hope so.

1021
01:11:41,275 --> 01:11:43,066
<i>You're still here?</i>

1022
01:11:45,446 --> 01:11:48,281
I thought you were supposed
to disappear. Or I was.

1023
01:11:48,532 --> 01:11:50,192
Not until 6.

1024
01:11:51,076 --> 01:11:52,487
You rat!

1025
01:11:52,744 --> 01:11:54,571
I never said midnight.

1026
01:11:54,913 --> 01:11:57,369
You knew I was waiting for midnight.

1027
01:11:58,167 --> 01:11:59,577
Are you going to leave?

1028
01:12:03,380 --> 01:12:04,495
Good.

1029
01:12:15,184 --> 01:12:16,844
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

1030
01:12:18,354 --> 01:12:20,595
<i>It's all right.
You can fall asleep.</i>

1031
01:12:21,607 --> 01:12:23,932
<i>I promise I won't touch you.</i>

1032
01:12:24,651 --> 01:12:25,896
Much.

1033
01:12:27,237 --> 01:12:29,989
<i>It's all right. I'm not tired.</i>

1034
01:12:30,824 --> 01:12:32,484
What were you saying?

1035
01:12:33,911 --> 01:12:37,196
I think the last thing
that you heard was...

1036
01:12:37,456 --> 01:12:40,125
...only God could make a tree.

1037
01:12:40,376 --> 01:12:41,455
Really?

1038
01:13:19,623 --> 01:13:21,912
What I wanted to say was...

1039
01:13:23,669 --> 01:13:25,792
...I think you are the kindest...

1040
01:13:26,046 --> 01:13:28,584
...sweetest, prettiest person...

1041
01:13:29,091 --> 01:13:31,084
<i>...I've ever met in my life.</i>

1042
01:13:32,636 --> 01:13:34,843
<i>I've never seen anyone...</i>

1043
01:13:35,472 --> 01:13:37,964
<i>...that's nicer to people
than you are.</i>

1044
01:13:50,946 --> 01:13:52,986
And the first time I saw you...

1045
01:13:54,074 --> 01:13:56,316
...something happened to me.

1046
01:13:57,578 --> 01:13:59,701
I never told you...

1047
01:14:03,083 --> 01:14:05,491
...but I knew I wanted
to hold you...

1048
01:14:05,711 --> 01:14:07,585
...as hard as I could.

1049
01:14:20,559 --> 01:14:23,015
<i>I don't deserve someone like you.</i>

1050
01:14:26,857 --> 01:14:28,649
But if I ever could...

1051
01:14:30,111 --> 01:14:32,187
...I swear I would love you...

1052
01:14:32,571 --> 01:14:34,694
...for the rest of my life.

1053
01:14:39,286 --> 01:14:41,160
Did you say something?

1054
01:14:46,877 --> 01:14:48,455
Good night, Rita.

1055
01:14:49,672 --> 01:14:51,249
Good night, Phil.

1056
01:15:16,198 --> 01:15:19,532
<i>Campers, rise and shine!
Don't forget your booties,</i>

1057
01:15:19,744 --> 01:15:22,780
<i>- It's cold out there!
- It's cold every day,</i>

1058
01:15:22,997 --> 01:15:25,286
<i>- Is this Miami Beach?
- Not hardly!</i>

1059
01:16:00,701 --> 01:16:03,157
<i>Who wants coffee?
Get it while it's hot.</i>

1060
01:16:04,038 --> 01:16:05,201
Thanks, Phil.

1061
01:16:05,414 --> 01:16:06,244
Larry?

1062
01:16:06,499 --> 01:16:08,575
Skim milk, two sugar.

1063
01:16:08,835 --> 01:16:10,163
Thanks, Phil.

1064
01:16:10,378 --> 01:16:11,540
Pastry?

1065
01:16:11,796 --> 01:16:12,958
<i>We're setting up.</i>

1066
01:16:13,172 --> 01:16:14,964
Pastry, Larry?
Take your pick.

1067
01:16:16,217 --> 01:16:18,256
Thanks. Raspberry. Great.

1068
01:16:18,761 --> 01:16:21,928
I talked with Buster Green,
the head groundhog honcho.

1069
01:16:22,181 --> 01:16:24,968
<i>He said if we set up here
we'll get a better shot.</i>

1070
01:16:25,435 --> 01:16:27,676
- What do you think?
- Sounds good.

1071
01:16:28,020 --> 01:16:29,219
Larry?

1072
01:16:30,523 --> 01:16:32,432
<i>Yeah. Let's go for it.</i>

1073
01:16:32,692 --> 01:16:33,723
Good work, Phil.

1074
01:16:34,402 --> 01:16:37,735
<i>Maybe we'll get lucky.
Let me give you a hand.</i>

1075
01:16:39,198 --> 01:16:42,116
<i>No, no. You got your coffee.
I'll get it.</i>

1076
01:16:43,411 --> 01:16:45,285
We never talk.
Do you have kids?

1077
01:17:20,073 --> 01:17:21,899
<i>I'd like a piano lesson.</i>

1078
01:17:22,241 --> 01:17:26,191
<i>I'm with a student. But if you
want to come back tomorrow...</i>

1079
01:17:26,412 --> 01:17:29,662
I kind of want to get started.
I can give you $1,000.

1080
01:17:32,418 --> 01:17:33,332
Come on in.

1081
01:17:52,897 --> 01:17:54,937
Morning!
Off to see the groundhog?

1082
01:17:55,149 --> 01:17:57,189
<i>Buon giorno, signore!</i>

1083
01:17:58,194 --> 01:18:00,650
<i>Think it'll be an early spring?</i>

1084
01:18:00,905 --> 01:18:03,277
<i>"Winter, slumbering in the open air</i>

1085
01:18:03,533 --> 01:18:05,157
Wears on his smiling face...

1086
01:18:05,410 --> 01:18:07,616
<i>...a dream of spring"</i>

1087
01:18:07,871 --> 01:18:08,902
Ciao!

1088
01:18:10,206 --> 01:18:11,404
Ciao!

1089
01:18:49,537 --> 01:18:50,782
How does she look?

1090
01:18:51,081 --> 01:18:52,160
Great.

1091
01:18:52,665 --> 01:18:53,579
Thank you.

1092
01:18:53,792 --> 01:18:57,243
Did you know he could ice sculpt?

1093
01:19:11,309 --> 01:19:14,512
Not bad. You say
this is your first lesson?

1094
01:19:15,480 --> 01:19:18,730
Yes, but my father
was a piano mover, so...

1095
01:19:24,656 --> 01:19:29,152
- Phil Connors, I thought it was you.
- Ned Ryerson.

1096
01:19:30,870 --> 01:19:33,408
I have missed you so much.

1097
01:19:37,794 --> 01:19:41,329
<i>I don't know where you're headed,
but can you call in sick?</i>

1098
01:19:44,759 --> 01:19:46,669
I got to get going.

1099
01:19:47,554 --> 01:19:49,593
<i>It's good to see you, Phil.</i>

1100
01:20:07,699 --> 01:20:09,158
Hello, father.

1101
01:20:09,910 --> 01:20:11,618
<i>Let's get you someplace warm.</i>

1102
01:20:13,455 --> 01:20:14,830
Remember me?

1103
01:20:21,671 --> 01:20:23,379
You brought the old man in?

1104
01:20:23,590 --> 01:20:24,621
How is he?

1105
01:20:25,342 --> 01:20:27,334
He just passed away.

1106
01:20:29,095 --> 01:20:32,132
- What did he die of?
- He was just old.

1107
01:20:32,390 --> 01:20:34,217
It was just his time.

1108
01:20:36,978 --> 01:20:39,979
- I want to see his chart. Excuse me.
- Sir!

1109
01:20:40,357 --> 01:20:41,981
<i>You can't come in here.</i>

1110
01:20:42,234 --> 01:20:44,855
Sir, this is a restricted area.

1111
01:20:54,037 --> 01:20:55,697
<i>Where's the chart?</i>

1112
01:20:56,206 --> 01:20:58,531
Sometimes people just die.

1113
01:20:59,459 --> 01:21:00,918
Not today.

1114
01:21:13,306 --> 01:21:15,513
Gets hard down there at the bottom.

1115
01:21:18,437 --> 01:21:19,635
Here you go.

1116
01:21:19,980 --> 01:21:21,094
Thank you.

1117
01:21:25,527 --> 01:21:26,606
Come on, dad.

1118
01:21:26,862 --> 01:21:28,237
Come on, pop.

1119
01:21:30,198 --> 01:21:31,990
Come on. Come on, breathe.

1120
01:21:32,242 --> 01:21:34,911
Breathe, pop! Breathe, pop!

1121
01:22:00,646 --> 01:22:03,315
When Chekhov saw the long winter...

1122
01:22:03,774 --> 01:22:07,143
...he saw a winter bleak
and dark and bereft of hope.

1123
01:22:07,402 --> 01:22:12,064
Yet we know winter is just
another step in the cycle of life.

1124
01:22:12,324 --> 01:22:15,989
But standing here among
the people of Punxsutawney...

1125
01:22:16,245 --> 01:22:19,032
...and basking in the warmth
of their hearths and hearts...

1126
01:22:20,123 --> 01:22:22,412
<i>...I couldn't imagine a better fate...</i>

1127
01:22:22,626 --> 01:22:25,580
...than a long and lustrous winter.

1128
01:22:25,837 --> 01:22:28,625
<i>From Punxsutawney, it's Phil Connors.</i>

1129
01:22:28,882 --> 01:22:30,163
So long.

1130
01:22:32,052 --> 01:22:33,760
Nice speech. Very nice.

1131
01:22:34,012 --> 01:22:35,175
Thank you.

1132
01:22:36,515 --> 01:22:39,765
- How was that for you two?
- My man, you touched me.

1133
01:22:40,018 --> 01:22:41,678
- Thanks, Larry.
- Thank you.

1134
01:22:43,063 --> 01:22:43,976
I got to go.

1135
01:22:45,566 --> 01:22:49,610
<i>That was surprising.
I didn't know you were so versatile.</i>

1136
01:22:49,862 --> 01:22:51,522
I surprise myself sometimes.

1137
01:22:51,738 --> 01:22:53,731
Would you like a cup of coffee?

1138
01:22:53,949 --> 01:22:57,899
<i>I'd love to. Can I have a rain check?
I've got some errands.</i>

1139
01:23:01,665 --> 01:23:03,574
Errands? What errands?

1140
01:23:03,834 --> 01:23:06,040
I thought we were going back.

1141
01:23:23,687 --> 01:23:26,522
What do you say?
What do you say?

1142
01:23:26,732 --> 01:23:29,602
You little brat.
You have never thanked me!

1143
01:23:30,319 --> 01:23:31,943
<i>I'll see you tomorrow...</i>

1144
01:23:32,196 --> 01:23:33,275
...maybe.

1145
01:23:40,996 --> 01:23:43,321
You totaled it.

1146
01:23:43,540 --> 01:23:47,668
<i>- It's only a flat tire.
- What are we going to do?</i>

1147
01:23:49,046 --> 01:23:52,462
<i>- It's an earthquake!
- It's not an earthquake.</i>

1148
01:23:52,675 --> 01:23:53,670
What is it?

1149
01:23:57,262 --> 01:23:59,338
Thank you, young man.

1150
01:24:00,474 --> 01:24:02,846
<i>It's nothing.
I had the tire and the jack.</i>

1151
01:24:03,102 --> 01:24:05,723
<i>Just be comfortable.
It'll be a minute.</i>

1152
01:24:05,980 --> 01:24:07,178
Who is that?

1153
01:24:07,439 --> 01:24:10,191
He must be from the motor club.

1154
01:24:11,443 --> 01:24:14,113
<i>He's having a heart attack!
Do something!</i>

1155
01:24:14,363 --> 01:24:18,443
Call 411, an ambulance, a lawyer,
doctor, anything!

1156
01:24:25,708 --> 01:24:27,250
I think that did it.

1157
01:24:31,130 --> 01:24:34,000
<i>If you're going to eat steak,
get sharper teeth.</i>

1158
01:24:34,258 --> 01:24:36,583
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

1159
01:24:37,177 --> 01:24:38,506
Who was that?

1160
01:24:38,721 --> 01:24:41,425
<i>- I'm fine, I'm fine.
- Are you sure?</i>

1161
01:24:41,682 --> 01:24:42,547
Eat, eat!

1162
01:24:46,979 --> 01:24:48,521
<i>People don't understand,,,</i>

1163
01:24:48,731 --> 01:24:51,518
<i>...what's involved.
This is an art form.</i>

1164
01:24:51,775 --> 01:24:54,231
I think most people just think...

1165
01:24:54,486 --> 01:24:57,653
...that I hold a camera
and point it at stuff.

1166
01:24:57,907 --> 01:25:00,195
<i>There's a lot more to it than that.</i>

1167
01:25:02,244 --> 01:25:05,744
Would you be interested in seeing
the inside of a van?

1168
01:25:05,956 --> 01:25:09,242
You know, I really have to
get back to the party.

1169
01:25:09,502 --> 01:25:11,210
<i>Great idea.
I'll go with you.</i>

1170
01:25:11,462 --> 01:25:13,704
Let me just drop a tip here.

1171
01:25:19,762 --> 01:25:21,256
Hi! How are you?

1172
01:25:21,514 --> 01:25:23,305
Rita, this is Nancy.

1173
01:25:24,433 --> 01:25:26,675
We were going to the party.
You going?

1174
01:25:26,894 --> 01:25:29,515
Sounds like fun.
Maybe we should call Phil.

1175
01:25:30,606 --> 01:25:32,682
<i>I think he's already in there.</i>

1176
01:27:29,392 --> 01:27:30,637
<i>Isn't he good?</i>

1177
01:27:30,893 --> 01:27:32,008
<i>He's great!</i>

1178
01:27:32,270 --> 01:27:33,894
<i>He's my student.</i>

1179
01:27:36,524 --> 01:27:38,398
<i>I'm so proud.</i>

1180
01:27:39,569 --> 01:27:40,767
Thank you.

1181
01:27:41,946 --> 01:27:43,986
Hello, welcome to our party.

1182
01:27:44,240 --> 01:27:46,482
<i>I didn't know you could
play like that.</i>

1183
01:27:46,742 --> 01:27:48,450
<i>I'm versatile.</i>

1184
01:27:55,835 --> 01:27:58,871
<i>It's that nice young man
from the motor club.</i>

1185
01:27:59,088 --> 01:28:00,582
Thank you again.

1186
01:28:00,840 --> 01:28:02,251
<i>It's nothing, ladies.</i>

1187
01:28:02,508 --> 01:28:05,758
<i>He's the fastest jack
in Jefferson County.</i>

1188
01:28:08,222 --> 01:28:09,847
What was that all about?

1189
01:28:10,099 --> 01:28:13,184
<i>Don't know. They've been
hitting on me all night.</i>

1190
01:28:14,062 --> 01:28:15,437
There you are!

1191
01:28:17,398 --> 01:28:20,601
I never thanked you properly
for what you did.

1192
01:28:20,860 --> 01:28:22,900
<i>He would've choked for sure.</i>

1193
01:28:23,154 --> 01:28:26,855
He may have. He was trying
to swallow a whole cow.

1194
01:28:27,116 --> 01:28:28,314
I owe you one, buddy.

1195
01:28:28,576 --> 01:28:31,696
<i>Hang on to him, dear.
He's a real find.</i>

1196
01:28:34,123 --> 01:28:35,831
What did you do today?

1197
01:28:36,084 --> 01:28:37,661
Same old, same old.

1198
01:28:43,424 --> 01:28:44,966
Excuse me, Mr. Connors.

1199
01:28:45,176 --> 01:28:46,754
Fred, how was the wedding?

1200
01:28:47,011 --> 01:28:50,012
Thank you for making
Debbie go through with it.

1201
01:28:50,265 --> 01:28:53,301
All I did was fan her flame
of passion for you.

1202
01:28:53,559 --> 01:28:54,758
You are the best.

1203
01:28:55,019 --> 01:28:56,051
No, you are.

1204
01:28:56,312 --> 01:28:59,479
Rita, this is
Debbie and Fred Kleiser.

1205
01:28:59,732 --> 01:29:03,564
- Here you go, kids. Congratulations.
- What is this?

1206
01:29:04,028 --> 01:29:05,855
No way!

1207
01:29:06,114 --> 01:29:09,234
WrestleMania!
No way!

1208
01:29:10,201 --> 01:29:13,155
<i>How'd you know?
We'll be in Pittsburgh anyway!</i>

1209
01:29:13,413 --> 01:29:15,240
<i>Thank you. You're a real pal.</i>

1210
01:29:15,498 --> 01:29:17,372
Oh, this is the best.

1211
01:29:22,171 --> 01:29:23,582
<i>I don't understand.</i>

1212
01:29:23,840 --> 01:29:25,548
I guess not.

1213
01:29:26,050 --> 01:29:28,802
How does everyone know you?
You come once a year.

1214
01:29:29,053 --> 01:29:30,880
<i>You're the most popular
person in town.</i>

1215
01:29:31,139 --> 01:29:33,345
Excuse me, Dr. Connors?

1216
01:29:33,558 --> 01:29:36,475
<i>I want to thank you
for fixing Felix's back.</i>

1217
01:29:36,686 --> 01:29:38,762
He can help around the house again.

1218
01:29:38,980 --> 01:29:41,471
<i>Well, I'm sorry
to hear that, Felix.</i>

1219
01:29:43,860 --> 01:29:45,484
Dr. Connors?

1220
01:29:45,862 --> 01:29:48,187
<i>It's kind of an honorary title.</i>

1221
01:29:48,448 --> 01:29:50,025
What is going on?

1222
01:29:50,241 --> 01:29:51,273
<i>I really don't know.</i>

1223
01:29:51,534 --> 01:29:53,990
There is something
going on with you.

1224
01:29:54,579 --> 01:29:56,536
You want the long or short version?

1225
01:29:56,790 --> 01:29:59,625
<i>Let's start with the short
and go from there.</i>

1226
01:30:05,423 --> 01:30:07,416
Okay, folks, attention.

1227
01:30:08,218 --> 01:30:11,337
Time for the bachelor auction.
You know the rules.

1228
01:30:11,596 --> 01:30:14,052
All the eligible bachelors
come in front.

1229
01:30:14,349 --> 01:30:15,808
And you ladies...

1230
01:30:16,059 --> 01:30:17,387
...you bid on them!

1231
01:30:17,644 --> 01:30:19,683
Do whatever you want with them...

1232
01:30:19,938 --> 01:30:21,515
...no questions asked!

1233
01:30:21,773 --> 01:30:24,857
<i>I don't want to know about it,
as long as it's legal.</i>

1234
01:30:25,068 --> 01:30:29,445
<i>Get out your pocketbooks,
and remember it's all for charity.</i>

1235
01:30:31,616 --> 01:30:33,194
What are you doing down here?

1236
01:30:33,451 --> 01:30:34,945
Go on, get up there.

1237
01:30:35,161 --> 01:30:38,246
<i>I got 10 bucks
that says you're mine.</i>

1238
01:30:38,665 --> 01:30:40,574
Buster, I got your first victim.

1239
01:30:40,792 --> 01:30:43,461
Phil Connors, come on up here!

1240
01:30:48,508 --> 01:30:51,842
All right! Now, what am I bid
for this fine specimen?

1241
01:30:52,137 --> 01:30:53,547
Five dollars!

1242
01:30:53,763 --> 01:30:55,720
The bidding has begun
at five dollars.

1243
01:30:56,016 --> 01:30:57,261
Ten dollars!

1244
01:30:57,475 --> 01:30:58,673
Fifteen!

1245
01:30:58,893 --> 01:31:00,886
- Twenty!
- Twenty-five!

1246
01:31:01,104 --> 01:31:02,053
Thirty!

1247
01:31:02,272 --> 01:31:04,063
- Thirty-five!
- Forty!

1248
01:31:04,274 --> 01:31:05,270
Forty-five!

1249
01:31:05,942 --> 01:31:06,973
Fifty!

1250
01:31:07,235 --> 01:31:08,184
Fifty-five!

1251
01:31:08,403 --> 01:31:09,399
Sixty!

1252
01:31:09,613 --> 01:31:11,273
<i>I'm bid $60.
Do I hear more?</i>

1253
01:31:15,076 --> 01:31:18,243
$339.88.

1254
01:31:22,167 --> 01:31:25,999
<i>We won't accept any more bids.
I think that's sold...</i>

1255
01:31:26,254 --> 01:31:29,919
...to the little lady for $339.88!

1256
01:31:31,051 --> 01:31:32,426
Congratulations!

1257
01:31:40,519 --> 01:31:42,428
<i>Okay, bachelors, who's next?</i>

1258
01:31:52,864 --> 01:31:56,150
All right! Now, what am I
bid for this guy?

1259
01:31:56,368 --> 01:31:58,195
Do I hear a buck and a half?

1260
01:31:58,495 --> 01:31:59,740
Anybody?

1261
01:32:00,622 --> 01:32:01,653
75 cents?

1262
01:32:01,873 --> 01:32:03,665
I bid a twopence!

1263
01:32:04,292 --> 01:32:06,665
Sold to the lady for 25 cents.

1264
01:32:06,878 --> 01:32:08,420
I got him!

1265
01:32:16,680 --> 01:32:19,385
Phil Connors,
I thought that was you.

1266
01:32:19,641 --> 01:32:22,097
This is Ned Ryerson,
my new insurance agent.

1267
01:32:22,352 --> 01:32:23,597
<i>I'll say.</i>

1268
01:32:24,813 --> 01:32:26,770
<i>I haven't seen him for 20 years.</i>

1269
01:32:27,023 --> 01:32:32,065
He comes up and buys whole life,
term, fire, auto, dental, health...

1270
01:32:32,279 --> 01:32:35,196
...with the optional death
and dismemberment plan.

1271
01:32:35,449 --> 01:32:37,607
This is the best day of my life.

1272
01:32:37,868 --> 01:32:39,991
- Mine too.
- Mine too.

1273
01:32:40,203 --> 01:32:41,448
Where are we going?

1274
01:32:41,705 --> 01:32:43,413
<i>Let's not spoil it.</i>

1275
01:32:44,958 --> 01:32:47,579
<i>Let's not...
I got that.</i>

1276
01:32:50,505 --> 01:32:51,916
<i>Why can't I look?</i>

1277
01:32:52,382 --> 01:32:54,209
Because you bother me a lot.

1278
01:32:54,509 --> 01:32:55,885
<i>I'm getting cold.</i>

1279
01:32:56,094 --> 01:32:57,719
How long do I have to sit here?

1280
01:32:58,347 --> 01:33:01,466
<i>I'm giving you your money's worth.
You paid top dollar for me.</i>

1281
01:33:02,059 --> 01:33:04,384
Well, I think you were a bargain.

1282
01:33:05,228 --> 01:33:07,351
<i>Sweet of you to say.
You're right.</i>

1283
01:33:10,108 --> 01:33:11,519
Is it finished yet?

1284
01:33:12,402 --> 01:33:15,273
I still have to put
cherry syrup on the top...

1285
01:33:15,489 --> 01:33:16,520
...then we can eat it.

1286
01:33:16,782 --> 01:33:19,451
<i>Come on, Phil.
I'm freezing!</i>

1287
01:33:19,660 --> 01:33:21,320
One second, one second.

1288
01:33:21,578 --> 01:33:23,370
Let me turn it in the light.

1289
01:33:28,877 --> 01:33:30,371
<i>It's amazing.</i>

1290
01:33:31,129 --> 01:33:32,374
<i>It's beautiful.</i>

1291
01:33:36,677 --> 01:33:38,052
How did you do that?

1292
01:33:38,887 --> 01:33:42,671
<i>I know your face so well,
I could've done it with my eyes closed.</i>

1293
01:33:47,229 --> 01:33:48,640
<i>It's lovely.</i>

1294
01:33:49,398 --> 01:33:51,225
<i>I don't know what to say.</i>

1295
01:33:52,442 --> 01:33:53,641
I do.

1296
01:33:55,737 --> 01:33:58,026
No matter what happens tomorrow...

1297
01:33:58,282 --> 01:34:00,155
...or for the rest of my life...

1298
01:34:00,367 --> 01:34:02,075
<i>...I'm happy now...</i>

1299
01:34:03,287 --> 01:34:04,864
...because I love you.

1300
01:34:05,789 --> 01:34:07,581
<i>I think I'm happy too.</i>

1301
01:35:06,266 --> 01:35:07,429
<i>Please, Not again,</i>

1302
01:35:07,643 --> 01:35:09,517
<i>- That's a great song,
- It's not,</i>

1303
01:35:09,770 --> 01:35:11,809
<i>Don't listen to this man...</i>

1304
01:35:12,398 --> 01:35:14,805
<i>It's too early.</i>

1305
01:35:25,536 --> 01:35:27,327
Something is different.

1306
01:35:27,955 --> 01:35:29,200
Good or bad?

1307
01:35:29,581 --> 01:35:31,870
Anything different is good.

1308
01:35:34,336 --> 01:35:36,625
But this could be real good.

1309
01:35:41,510 --> 01:35:42,921
Why are you here?

1310
01:35:43,387 --> 01:35:45,463
I bought you.
I own you.

1311
01:35:47,975 --> 01:35:49,553
But why are you still here?

1312
01:35:49,810 --> 01:35:52,894
<i>You said, "Stay,"
so I stayed.</i>

1313
01:35:55,566 --> 01:35:57,605
<i>I said, "Stay,"
so you stayed.</i>

1314
01:35:57,860 --> 01:36:00,398
<i>I can't even make a collie stay.</i>

1315
01:36:02,573 --> 01:36:04,566
I got to check something.

1316
01:36:05,367 --> 01:36:06,743
Stay.

1317
01:36:07,161 --> 01:36:08,275
Stay.

1318
01:36:13,918 --> 01:36:15,198
<i>They're gone!</i>

1319
01:36:16,128 --> 01:36:17,706
<i>They're all gone.</i>

1320
01:36:19,798 --> 01:36:22,503
- Do you know what today is?
- No, what?

1321
01:36:23,844 --> 01:36:25,837
Today is tomorrow.

1322
01:36:26,430 --> 01:36:27,759
It happened.

1323
01:36:30,017 --> 01:36:32,259
<i>- You're here.
- I'm here.</i>

1324
01:36:36,440 --> 01:36:41,067
<i>Why weren't you like this last night?
You just fell asleep.</i>

1325
01:36:42,905 --> 01:36:45,692
It was the end of a very long day.

1326
01:36:48,786 --> 01:36:52,570
Is there anything I can do
for you today?

1327
01:36:53,457 --> 01:36:56,079
<i>I'm sure I can think of something.</i>

1328
01:37:29,201 --> 01:37:31,194
<i>It's so beautiful!</i>

1329
01:37:41,839 --> 01:37:43,464
<i>Let's live here.</i>

1330
01:37:53,935 --> 01:37:55,974
<i>We'll rent to start.</i>

1331
01:41:00,580 --> 01:41:01,611
Subtitles by
